"{\"uid\": \"vogue.com-article-simone-biles-and-suni-lee-2024-olympics\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"It was another high-profile, high-flying night in Paris this evening, as Simone Biles and Suni Lee represented the United States in the women's individual all-around final.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 172, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 50, \"end\": 55, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.41717874006656e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 73, \"end\": 85, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Simone Biles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\"}, {\"begin\": 90, \"end\": 98, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sunisa_Lee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Suni Lee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sunisa_Lee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sunisa_Lee\"}, {\"begin\": 115, \"end\": 128, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9990755466590249, \"rank\": 0.0009138701957044861, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Back at the Bercy Arenaafter the USA claimed team gold on Tuesday, the pair competed before a crowd including Steph Curry, Martha Stewart, Seth Rogen, Tony Hawk, Kendall Jenner, Tony Parker, Bill Gates, and Zinedine Zidane.\", \"from\": 173, \"to\": 396, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 185, \"end\": 190, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Accor_Arena\", \"score\": 0.9920084601542634, \"rank\": 0.008055919042796133, \"text\": \"Bercy\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Accor_Arena\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Accor_Arena\"}, {\"begin\": 206, \"end\": 209, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9996427808960743, \"rank\": 0.000327757851205874, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 283, \"end\": 294, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Curry\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Steph Curry\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Curry\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephen_Curry\"}, {\"begin\": 296, \"end\": 310, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Martha_Stewart\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.184594630149219e-39, \"text\": \"Martha Stewart\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Martha_Stewart\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Martha_Stewart\"}, {\"begin\": 312, \"end\": 322, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seth_Rogen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Seth Rogen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seth_Rogen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seth_Rogen\"}, {\"begin\": 335, \"end\": 349, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kendall_Jenner\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kendall Jenner\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q4610556\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kendall_Jenner\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kendall_Jenner\"}, {\"begin\": 351, \"end\": 362, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Parker\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2659123989832964e-13, \"text\": \"Tony Parker\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Parker\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Parker\"}, {\"begin\": 364, \"end\": 374, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bill_Gates\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.7923902937250905e-27, \"text\": \"Bill Gates\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bill_Gates\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bill_Gates\"}, {\"begin\": 380, \"end\": 395, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zinedine_Zidane\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Zinedine Zidane\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q628099\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zinedine_Zidane\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zinedine_Zidane\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There, Biles's overall score of 59.131 won her another gold medal-ratcheting her career tally up to six-while Brazil's Rebeca Andrade captured the silver and Lee won the bronze.\", \"from\": 398, \"to\": 575, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 508, \"end\": 514, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9929034114568396, \"rank\": 0.0069271150447400565, \"text\": \"Brazil\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 517, \"end\": 531, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rebeca_Andrade\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rebeca Andrade\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rebeca_Andrade\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rebeca_Andrade\"}, {\"begin\": 556, \"end\": 559, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\", \"score\": 0.9972545901043365, \"rank\": 0.002752955346521458, \"text\": \"Lee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With today's result, Biles became only the third woman in history to win two individual all-around golds at the Olympics, following the Soviet Union's Larisa Latynina (in 1956 and 1960) and Czechoslovakia's Vera Caslavska (in 1964 and 1968).\", \"from\": 576, \"to\": 817, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 719, \"end\": 724, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999992846824, \"rank\": 7.1363821662093e-10, \"text\": \"Union\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 727, \"end\": 742, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Larisa_Latynina\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Larisa Latynina\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Larisa_Latynina\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Larisa_Latynina\"}, {\"begin\": 766, \"end\": 780, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Czechoslovakia_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"score\": 0.8627302337326105, \"rank\": 0.1238318186302872, \"text\": \"Czechoslovakia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Czechoslovakia_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Czechoslovakia_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\"}, {\"begin\": 783, \"end\": 787, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vera_Duckworth\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.699996563526345e-23, \"text\": \"Vera\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vera_Duckworth\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vera_Duckworth\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"During the individual all-around, competitors wear their own leotards.\", \"from\": 819, \"to\": 889, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Biles's had a blue base with dazzling allover embellishments, while Lee's had more of an ombr\\u00e9 scheme, blending blue and red with an almost Art Deco-style filigree.\", \"from\": 890, \"to\": 1054, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 958, \"end\": 961, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\", \"score\": 0.9972545901043365, \"rank\": 0.002752955346521458, \"text\": \"Lee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Both looks were covered in crystals, befitting Team USA's starry status.\", \"from\": 1055, \"to\": 1127, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1102, \"end\": 1110, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999787161741948, \"rank\": 1.0664762196321677e-05, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As expected, Biles-the most decorated gymnast in history-performed her modified version of the Yurchenko double pike on vault, a move that no one had landed at theOlympic Gamesuntil Biles pulled it off in Paris's qualifying rounds.\", \"from\": 1129, \"to\": 1360, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1224, \"end\": 1233, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yurchenko_(vault)\", \"score\": 0.9924615128803714, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Yurchenko\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yurchenko_(vault)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yurchenko_(vault)\"}, {\"begin\": 1334, \"end\": 1339, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.41717874006656e-16, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Notably, she did not perform it during the team event; it's a risky, gutsy skill, and Biles and company were said to want to preserve said risk for the individual competition.\", \"from\": 1361, \"to\": 1536, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Well, that strategy paid off: Biles's score of 15.766 quickly put her in the lead.\", \"from\": 1537, \"to\": 1619, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Next came the uneven bars.\", \"from\": 1621, \"to\": 1647, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After Andrade's routine, it was nice to see her and Biles exchange big smiles and a double fist bump.\", \"from\": 1648, \"to\": 1749, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1654, \"end\": 1661, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrade_El_Idolo\", \"score\": 0.999999999994543, \"rank\": 5.600147864994688e-12, \"text\": \"Andrade\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13474373\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrade_El_Idolo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrade_El_Idolo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Biles received a steep deduction when it was her turn; she had too much swing going into her Pak Salto.\", \"from\": 1750, \"to\": 1853, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1843, \"end\": 1852, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pak_salto\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pak Salto\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pak_salto\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pak_salto\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After the second rotation, Andrade took the lead, with Algeria's Kaylia Nemour in the silver-medal position.\", \"from\": 1854, \"to\": 1962, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1881, \"end\": 1888, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrade_El_Idolo\", \"score\": 0.999999999994543, \"rank\": 5.600147864994688e-12, \"text\": \"Andrade\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13474373\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrade_El_Idolo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrade_El_Idolo\"}, {\"begin\": 1909, \"end\": 1916, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.7128917572800059, \"rank\": 0.40273683830534135, \"text\": \"Algeria\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Biles was in third.\", \"from\": 1963, \"to\": 1982, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For their third rotation, Biles and Lee headed to the beam.\", \"from\": 1984, \"to\": 2043, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2020, \"end\": 2023, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\", \"score\": 0.9972545901043365, \"rank\": 0.002752955346521458, \"text\": \"Lee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Biles in particular had a great showing, overtaking the lead from Andrade going into their final discipline: the floor.\", \"from\": 2044, \"to\": 2163, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2110, \"end\": 2117, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrade_El_Idolo\", \"score\": 0.999999999994543, \"rank\": 5.600147864994688e-12, \"text\": \"Andrade\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13474373\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrade_El_Idolo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrade_El_Idolo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The atmosphere was tense as the crowd waited for the Brazilian's score-Andrade went last-to see where things stood.\", \"from\": 2164, \"to\": 2279, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Lee was beaming after sticking her first pass, and when her floor routine ended, the cheers were earsplittingly loud.\", \"from\": 2281, \"to\": 2398, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2281, \"end\": 2284, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\", \"score\": 0.9972545901043365, \"rank\": 0.002752955346521458, \"text\": \"Lee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(Lee was the defending all-around gold medalist, after all.)\", \"from\": 2399, \"to\": 2459, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2400, \"end\": 2403, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\", \"score\": 0.9972545901043365, \"rank\": 0.002752955346521458, \"text\": \"Lee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With a total score of 56.465, Lee was guaranteed a medal at this stage.\", \"from\": 2460, \"to\": 2531, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2490, \"end\": 2493, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\", \"score\": 0.9972545901043365, \"rank\": 0.002752955346521458, \"text\": \"Lee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Andrade looked good on the floor but stepped out of bounds, which stymied her chances of getting back to gold-medal position.\", \"from\": 2533, \"to\": 2658, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2533, \"end\": 2540, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrade_El_Idolo\", \"score\": 0.999999999994543, \"rank\": 5.600147864994688e-12, \"text\": \"Andrade\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13474373\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrade_El_Idolo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrade_El_Idolo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But Biles-in dominant fashion-had a near-flawless turn, soaring somehow ever higher than usual.\", \"from\": 2659, \"to\": 2754, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"When the music ended, she knew, and so did the crowd-this was gold, once again.\", \"from\": 2755, \"to\": 2834, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Her score of 15.066 sealed the deal.\", \"from\": 2835, \"to\": 2871, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Of US women's gymnastics performances at these Games, Lee previously told the press: \\\"It's just different this time around\\u2026.\", \"from\": 2873, \"to\": 2997, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2876, \"end\": 2878, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9998557088510841, \"rank\": 0.0001442978555546771, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2927, \"end\": 2930, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\", \"score\": 0.9972545901043365, \"rank\": 0.002752955346521458, \"text\": \"Lee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cliff_Lee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We had so many expectations on us, but we have done exactly what we were supposed to do.\\\"\", \"from\": 2998, \"to\": 3087, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Have they ever.\", \"from\": 3088, \"to\": 3103, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Everything You Need to Know About the 2024 Olympics  The Best Olympic Uniforms at the Summer 2024 Games  From the Archives: Olympians inVogue  The Best Olympic Movies to Watch Ahead of the Paris Games  Before the Games Begin, Pharrell Williams, Charlize Theron, Serena Williams, Rosal\\u00eda, and Omar Sy Will Co-Host a Prelude to the Olympics      \\u00a92025Cond\\u00e9 Nast.\", \"from\": 3105, \"to\": 3465, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3331, \"end\": 3348, \"title\": \"htt